comment.body:
> > Please note that there is some known issues in OTX1.x with torch2.0.1. #2451
> > I'm not sure whether we have plan to enable NNCF QAT on OTX2.0, though.
> 
> Yes, that's right, I'm afraid that optimization for OTX 2.0 is still uncharted territory. @samet-akcay We don't think hard enough about optimization. We need a good design and I think we need to find an issue with optimization side.

I think we need to have a clear list of requirements first. There is a bit of uncertainty there unfortunately. Once we know what exactly we need to support, we could then initiate some discussions with the nncf folks to have a clear design

issue.body:
### Summary

- Upgrade to torch==2.0.1
- Remove black
Replace black with ruff. According to the author of ruff, it is 30x faster than black and 99% compatible. As can be seen from the changes, it is indeed compatible in our case. comment.body:
> Please note that there is some known issues in OTX1.x with torch2.0.1. #2451
> 
> I'm not sure whether we have plan to enable NNCF QAT on OTX2.0, though.

Yes, that's right, I'm afraid that optimizing for OTX 2.0 is still uncharted territory.
@samet-akcay We don't think hard enough about optimization. We need a good design and I think we need to find an issue with optimization side.
